<doc id="627795" wikidata="Q943829" url="?curid=627795" title="Rainy River District">
<text>Rainy River District is a district and census division in Northwestern Ontario in the Canadian province of Ontario. It was created in 1885. It is the only division in Ontario that lies completely in the Central Time Zone, except for the township of Atikokan (including Sapawe and Kawene to the east) observing Eastern Standard Time for part of the year. Its seat is Fort Frances. It is known for its fishing and its location on the US border opposite International Falls, Minnesota, and Baudette, Minnesota.

==Subdivisions==
Municipalities
Unorganized area:
* Rainy River, Unorganized (served by the Eva Marion Lake local services board)

===First Nations===
Reserves:

* Agency 1
* Assabaska
* Big Grassy River 35G
* Big Island 31D
* Big Island 31E
* Big Island 31F
* Big Island 37
* Big Island Mainland 93
* Couchiching 16A
* Lake of the Woods 31H
